      "demonstrative_example_id": "DX-39",
      "text": "\n               \u003cIntro_Text\u003eThe following example attempts to resolve a hostname.\u003c/Intro_Text\u003e\n               \u003cExample_Code Nature=\"bad\" Language=\"Java\"\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:div\u003eprotected void doPost (HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws IOException {\u003cxhtml:div style=\"margin-left:10px;\"\u003eString ip = req.getRemoteAddr();\u003cxhtml:br/\u003eInetAddress addr = InetAddress.getByName(ip);\u003cxhtml:br/\u003e...\u003cxhtml:br/\u003eout.println(\"hello \" + addr.getHostName());\u003c/xhtml:div\u003e}\u003c/xhtml:div\u003e\n               \u003c/Example_Code\u003e\n               \u003cBody_Text\u003eA DNS lookup failure will cause the Servlet to throw an exception.\u003c/Body_Text\u003e\n            "
    }
